<div id="Item_0" class="PageTitle"><div class="Options"></div><h1>Burkardt and Thomas' Altian insurgency diary</h1></div>

<div id="Discussion_12165" class="Item ItemDiscussion">
    <div class="Discussion">
        <div class="Item-Header DiscussionHeader">
            <div class="AuthorWrap">
            <span class="Author">
                <a title="PFC Thomas" href="https://vanilla.29th.org/profile/PFC%20Thomas" class="PhotoWrap"><img src="../../uploads/userpics/657/nKIE8CTV46CT2.png" alt="PFC Thomas" class="ProfilePhoto ProfilePhotoMedium" /></a><a href="https://vanilla.29th.org/profile/PFC%20Thomas" class="Username">PFC Thomas</a>            </span>
            <span class="AuthorInfo">
                            </span>
            </div>
            <div class="Meta DiscussionMeta">
            <span class="MItem DateCreated">
                <a href="burkardt-and-thomas-altian-insurgency-diary" class="Permalink" rel="nofollow"><time title="June 8, 2016 1:55PM" datetime="2016-06-08T13:55:37+00:00">June 2016</time></a>            </span>
                <span class="MItem"> <span title="Edited September 3, 2016 7:50PM by Cpt. Hill [Ret.]." class="DateUpdated">edited September 2016</span> </span>                 <span class="MItem Category"> in <a href="../../categories/public-discussion">Public Discussion</a></span>             </div>
        </div>
                <div class="Item-BodyWrap">
            <div class="Item-Body">
                <div class="Message userContent">
                    <p>So PFC Burkardt and I decided to have some fun with an Arma 3 scenario called "Antistasi", which basically allows you to become part of the resistance fighting against the puppet regime of Altis. Part of being a rebel is to know where and when to fight/retreat. Fighting against a professional army, the Altis Armed Forces, requires a lot of effort, and 2 people cannot fight against a well armed, well trained fighting force, so every help is needed!<br />
On the first day, we assaulted an outpost and managed to overrun the garrison. However they managed to call in reinforcement but before that reinforcement even cock their guns PFC Burkardt blew an AT right at 'em<br />
Needless to say it was kinda unhealthy for the occupants of the truck<br />
<a rel="nofollow" href="http://s1202.photobucket.com/user/thomashung1/media/107410_20160604012248_1.png.html"><img src="http://i1202.photobucket.com/albums/bb366/thomashung1/107410_20160604012248_1.png" border="0" alt="photo 107410_20160604012248_1.png" /></a><br />
Several days later we decided to raid an outpost near an AAF airbase, the raid went well and we managed to kill all of the troops garrisoned there. But once again their magical radio managed to call in a transport helicopter. PFC Burkardt once again saved the day with his trusty AA Missile, but in the crashing process the transport helo crashed into the very same guard tower I was residing in, the resulting scream of desperation woke up 2 of my housemates<br />
<img src="http://images.akamai.steamusercontent.com/ugc/440605165225106898/22757A1A0EE2893398D440F0D429E26403B5D6C0/" alt="enter image description here" title="enter image title here" /><br />
After this the AAF decided that they've had enough and sent in 2 IFV to wipe us, but we managed to sneak away<br />
Wanna know what happened next? Tune in for the next page in our diary!</p>
                </div>
                <div class="Reactions"></div>            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
