                <div class="Item-BodyWrap">
                    <div class="Item-Body">
                        <div class="Message userContent">
                            <p>So for today's activity we continue on from the last time, having escaped the QRF sent to deal with us<br />
The IFVs decided to stay at the outpost to act as deterrence against any future attacks by us. Of course the only logical choice for us insurgents must only be assaulting the outpost again <img class="emoji" src="../../resources/emoji/lol.png" title=":D" alt=":D" height="20" /><br />
So, we snuck in, luckily there was no infantry support (no wonder why the AAF is kinda losing), and we managed to got behind one of the 2 IFVs. We popped the rear wheels, killed the occupants, and used the mounted AGL to take out the other IFV<br />
<img src="http://i1202.photobucket.com/albums/bb366/thomashung1/107410_20160609053445_1.png" alt="enter image description here" title="enter image title here" /><br />
Having secured some heavy weapons like the one above and some other HMG, we decided to set our eyes on the nearby airport, with 4 fuel trucks and 2 transport helicopters which are guaranteed to yield a hefty sum to fund our war effort against the Puppet Regime.<br />
When we got near the airfield, we were spotted by a Hellcat! Scary. But PFC Burkardt the Vehicle Bane once again demonstrated his weird affinity with destroying stuffs, this time with an anti-materiel rifle (I **** you guys not he did it, the absolute mad man)<br />
<img src="http://i1202.photobucket.com/albums/bb366/thomashung1/107410_20160609053522_1.png" alt="enter image description here" title="enter image title here" /><br />
<img src="http://i1202.photobucket.com/albums/bb366/thomashung1/107410_20160609053532_1.png" alt="enter image description here" title="enter image title here" /><br />
We were going to continue our assault until a large size QRF force from one of the main AAF bases decided to roll upon us. The IFV got destroyed and PFC Burkardt got wounded. I popped some smoke and carried him safely back to our base.<br />
Stay tuned for other awesome stories in Burkardt and Thomas' AWESOME! Altian insurgency diary !!!</p>

<hr />

<p>If you guys want to help with the war effort, we use the mod set for Arma 3, which can be found <a rel="nofollow" href="http://withsix.com/p/Arma-3/collections/yG230HXpyUeimosehvsCWg/29th-ID-(Required)">here</a><br />
This is not a constantly hosted server, so if you want to join you can either contact:<br />
<a rel="nofollow" href="http://steamcommunity.com/id/TomHung/">PFC Thomas</a><br />
<a rel="nofollow" href="http://steamcommunity.com/profiles/76561198062378256">PFC Burkardt</a><br />
Ever Forward! (and down with Altis Puppet Regime, Vivé la Revolucion)</p>
