                <div class="Item-BodyWrap">
                    <div class="Item-Body">
                        <div class="Message userContent">
                            <p>A pleasure to have such interest in our efforts and woes as the spearhead of a glorious, but difficult, revolution.</p>

<p>I will be booting up our first start on the Coy. Server within the next hour. With that being said:<br />
<strong>If you are unfamiliar with the mission Antistasi please please please, at minimal, read briefly the overview of how the scenario works.</strong></p>

<p>This scenario is extremely complex and has a lot of cool underlying features such as <strong>going undercover</strong> as a rebel and infiltrating hostile zones. If you do not read how to activate the custom menus and what they do <strong>you will be less effective</strong> as a participating rebel.</p>

<p>We in this rebellion are all soldiers, but we are all soldiers with purpose and (extremely limited) resources.<br />
Wasteful uses of our equipment in this scenario will likely end in eradication of everything we gained.</p>

<p>I guess three points to take from this would be:<br />
<strong>1. Read Briefing so you know what to do in case one of the more experienced (in regards to the scenario) are not present</strong></p>

<p><strong>2. BRING FRIENDS. This AI means serious business when it attacks. Full platoons and mechanized units will assault that $20 tent you just captured just because they can and that happened to be their favorite tent.</strong></p>

<p><strong>3. Scavenge. Our resources are pitiful until we gather them. Capture vehicles, guns, equipment, prisoners. Anything that helps bolster our forces will be put to good use.</strong></p>

<p><em>disclaimer</em><br />
This Scenario is not optimized to be played with our full modset. That being said, everything works as it is intended with exceptions of: MINES, and Titan AT (doesn't lock, but yes Titan AA still works)</p>

<p><strong>P.S.<br />
AIT's are still to be adhered to on the Coy. Server as per Chief's command and upholding 29th Standards.</strong><br />
Do not hesitate to ask questions. What I've learned is all from trial and error.</p>

<p>Cheers.<br />
Hope to see some support and rootin' tootin' gun shootin' rebels out there to show these AI how the 29th rolls.</p>

<p>-Burky</p>

<p>-edit-<br />
Will be hosting some practice while I wait for CP2S3 Drills to complete today</p>

<p>Feel free to join me <img class="emoji" src="../../resources/emoji/smile.png" title=":)" alt=":)" height="20" /></p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="Reactions"></div>                    </div>
