                <div class="Item-BodyWrap">
                    <div class="Item-Body">
                        <div class="Message userContent">
                            <p>(Continuing on...)<br />
Our situation was bleak: PFC Burkardt lost his trusty anti-materiel rifle and we lost our only heavy vehicle; a large AAF Strike Force was situated right nearby our HQ and we didn't have any heavy weapon to defend ourselves. Then suddenly, our long range radio picked up a NATO signal coming from its carrier in the Mediterranean Sea. On the other side was an USA Officer, Jason Hill. He said that our distress signal had been picked up and our fight for freedom hadn't gone unnoticed. Officer Hill further elaborated that an US Army unit, Charlie Company of the 1st Battalion, 29th Infantry Division will be dispatched to help in our fight, but they must have time to make preparations. So for the mean time NATO will negotiate with the AAF Puppet Regime to buy time for us Rebels to relocate deep into the forests of Western Altis.<br />
For the time being, we would be assisted by 2 Charlie Company soldiers: Sgt. Nelson who specializes in what he calls "Hustlin'" and T/5 Zim who specializes in jungle warfare because he lives in the jungle<br />
<img src="http://i1202.photobucket.com/albums/bb366/thomashung1/107410_20160610235945_1.png" alt="enter image description here" title="enter image title here" /><br />
Their assistance immediately took effect when they instructed us on assaulting an AAF Outpost located on a green energy farm near the town of Oreokastro. The initial assault was very bad, but with their help we managed to wipe out the AAF Garrison and even pushed back an air counter-attack by AAF Airborne troops<br />
<img src="http://i1202.photobucket.com/albums/bb366/thomashung1/107410_20160610233829_1.png" alt="enter image description here" title="enter image title here" /><br />
<img src="http://i1202.photobucket.com/albums/bb366/thomashung1/107410_20160610233956_1.png" alt="enter image description here" title="enter image title here" /><br />
Several hours later we received intel from our hidden observation groups that an AAF convoy was making its way towards our location, so Sgt. Nelson and T/5 Zim helped us commandeer an AAF Strider and an MG truck to ambush the convoy. The convoy consisted of an AFV and an HMG Strider, but accurate fire from PFC Burkardt's MG truck disabled the Strider and allowing me to destroy the AFV with a well placed RPG rocket<br />
<img src="http://i1202.photobucket.com/albums/bb366/thomashung1/107410_20160611003025_1.png" alt="enter image description here" title="enter image title here" /><br />
We ended the ambush with an assault on an another AAF Outpost nearby and got away with 3 newly acquired AAF vehicles which will undoubtedly contribute to the overall war effort against the tyranny that has been oppressing our people for years.<br />
The US advisors had to return to the NATO carrier to report the situation so we must end our day there.<br />
Hopefully in the future more help will come from our friends in NATO and freedom-fighters who cherish democracy and human rights like us!<br />
Ever Forward (and down with the Puppet Regime!!!)</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="Reactions"></div>                    </div>
