                <div class="Item-BodyWrap">
                    <div class="Item-Body">
                        <div class="Message userContent">
                            <h3>Beaten, battered, but never broken. The FIA Fight on.</h3>

<p><strong>-The Relocation-</strong><br />
While the struggle continues, assistance from NATO led to decisive gains for the FIA rebels today. Losses on both sides rose to new heights as armed resistance fighters pour into the ranks of the rebellion. With CSAT outspoken about NATO's involvement we could see increasing conflict from both sides if it escalates.</p>

<p>In today's development the FIA gained support from the local population despite their ferocious attacks on AAF medical convoys. Reports say that the escorts were, in fact, ambushed with RPGs and small arms fire. The convoy en route to supply the locals with much needed food, water, and medical equipment was completely destroyed. With disease on the rise inside a war torn country suggests the FIA may not be the good guys after all. Updates to come on reactions from Altas citizens on the efforts of these self dubbed "Freedom fighters".</p>

<h3>Now to footage captured from our insiders on the ground.</h3>

