                    <div class="Item-Body">
                        <div class="Message userContent">
                            <p><strong>THE REBELLION GROWS</strong><br />
After receiving extensive NATO support in the form of military advisor and covert strike force, the FIA fighters have managed to secure the wooded areas of North-Western Altis including an airport for NATO supply and a former AAF Firebase<br />
<img src="http://i1202.photobucket.com/albums/bb366/thomashung1/107410_20160618184422_1.png" alt="enter image description here" title="enter image title here" /></p>

<p>After receiving invaluable strategic advice from Officer Hill and Officer Bergstrom, a rebel strike force was sent down to take an AAF Outpost and Factory to the South West of the FIA-controlled territory<br />
<img src="http://i1202.photobucket.com/albums/bb366/thomashung1/107410_20160618192744_1.png" alt="enter image description here" title="enter image title here" /></p>

<p><em>Here the Rebel convoy is passing through an Outpost recently captured in previous operations</em><br />
<img src="http://i1202.photobucket.com/albums/bb366/thomashung1/107410_20160618192756_1.png" alt="enter image description here" title="enter image title here" /></p>

<p>An another 29th soldier First Sergeant Balzer can be seen moving into the town of Kore to provide intel for the main strike force. The town of Kore is a major economic target as its outskirt is the site for an industrial factory with valuable assets<br />
<img src="http://i1202.photobucket.com/albums/bb366/thomashung1/107410_20160618194649_1.png" alt="enter image description here" title="enter image title here" /></p>

<p>As the strike force is conducting assault on the factory, an AAF counterrattack threatened to overrun the FIA HQ itself. Scattered FIA members rallied to defend the area with the help of some new members of the European detachment of the 29th ID. Here PFC Murray, PFC Van Gastel and a familiar face PFC Danberg can be seen. PFC Van Gastel, along with the military advisors provided immense help to the defend of the area against a mechanized platoon of the AAF<br />
<img src="http://i1202.photobucket.com/albums/bb366/thomashung1/107410_20160618203232_1.png" alt="enter image description here" title="enter image title here" /></p>

<p>The battle concluded as the strike force successfully captured the factory and the AAF platoon pulverized with at least 2 trucks and 1 APC destroyed<br />
Combat has ceased for the time being as soldiers of the 29th regroup to conduct operational drilling<br />
Ever Forward!</p>
