                    <div class="Meta CommentMeta CommentInfo">
            <span class="MItem DateCreated">
               <a href="https://vanilla.29th.org/discussion/comment/56551/#Comment_56551" class="Permalink" name="Item_27" rel="nofollow"><time title="June 18, 2016 7:49PM" datetime="2016-06-18T19:49:29+00:00">June 2016</time></a>            </span>
                        <span class="MItem"> <span title="Edited June 18, 2016 7:56PM by PFC Burkardt [Ret.]." class="DateUpdated">edited June 2016</span> </span>                                            </div>
                </div>
                <div class="Item-BodyWrap">
                    <div class="Item-Body">
                        <div class="Message userContent">
                            <h3>Hell Claims only the guilty. War. . .War claims all.</h3>

<p><img src="http://images.akamai.steamusercontent.com/ugc/441731799627190459/3E36D20C1D063D2C8CF92033298A844F4C210EA8/" alt="enter image description here" title="Hell claims the guilty. War claims all." /></p>

<p><em>A note found crumpled in the hands of an AAF solider</em></p>

<p>Maybe we cannot understand this thing<br />
That makes these rebels die;<br />
And yet all things love freedom - and the Spring<br />
Clear in the sky;<br />
I think I would not do this deed again<br />
For all that I hold by;<br />
Gaze down my rifle at his breast - but then<br />
A soldier I.<br />
They say that he was kindly - different too,<br />
Apart from all the rest;<br />
A lover of the poor; and all shot through,<br />
His wounds ill drest,<br />
He came before us, faced us like a man,<br />
He knew a deeper pain<br />
Than blows or bullets - ere the world began;<br />
Died he in vain?<br />
Ready - present; And he just smiling - God!<br />
I felt my rifle shake<br />
His wounds were opened out and round that chair<br />
Was one red lake;<br />
I swear his lips said 'Fire!' when all was still<br />
Before my rifle spat<br />
That cursed lead - and I was picked to kill<br />
A man like that!</p>

<p><em>-Connolly<br />
by Liam MacGabhann</em></p>

<h3>Ever Forward</h3>

<p>The rebellion's advancement knows no end. Determined to free Altis from the vice grip of tyranny roars of battle rage across the land. Efforts to negotiate from both sides have met bitter ends. It seems the only language each understands is the sound of ordinance and rifle alike.</p>

<p>Until next time fellow Rebels. <br />
Fight on.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="Reactions"></div>                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </li>
                <li class="Item ItemComment isOriginalPoster" id="Comment_56734">
            <div class="Comment">

                                <div class="Options">
                                    </div>
                                <div class="Item-Header CommentHeader">
                    <div class="AuthorWrap">
            <span class="Author">
               <a title="PFC Thomas" href="https://vanilla.29th.org/profile/PFC%20Thomas" class="PhotoWrap"><img src="../../uploads/userpics/657/nKIE8CTV46CT2.png" alt="PFC Thomas" class="ProfilePhoto ProfilePhotoMedium" /></a><a href="https://vanilla.29th.org/profile/PFC%20Thomas" class="Username">PFC Thomas</a>            </span>
            <span class="AuthorInfo">
                             </span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="Meta CommentMeta CommentInfo">
            <span class="MItem DateCreated">
               <a href="https://vanilla.29th.org/discussion/comment/56734/#Comment_56734" class="Permalink" name="Item_28" rel="nofollow"><time title="June 20, 2016 8:24AM" datetime="2016-06-20T08:24:30+00:00">June 2016</time></a>            </span>
                                                                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="Item-BodyWrap">
                    <div class="Item-Body">
                        <div class="Message userContent">
                            <h3><strong>Tyranny Trembles</strong></h3>

<p>As the Rebellion grows in size and territory, the number of recruits is also increasing accordingly. From a 2-man squad to a platoon-size fighting force capable of multiple independent actions. Aside from fresh recruits, veterans of past conflict once again take up arms to free their island from utter corruption. Here Staff Sergeant Frank and Sergeant Erb can be seen re-familiarize themselves with the modern tools of killing. SSgt. Frank is a bitter veteran of the 2nd Altian Revolution, whose presence provides a reminder of the gritty revolution and calming aura on the recruits. Sgt. Erb was part of the 11th Regiment "Softballers" which took part in the decisive Siege of Kavala. <br />
<img src="http://i1202.photobucket.com/albums/bb366/thomashung1/107410_20160620024750_1.png" alt="enter image description here" title="enter image title here" /><br />
Here the rebel force can be seen in Company formation, disciplined by SSgt. Frank and commanded by anonymous NATO Officer<br />
<img src="http://i1202.photobucket.com/albums/bb366/thomashung1/107410_20160620025951_1.png" alt="enter image description here" title="enter image title here" /></p>

<p>To test the skills of new recruits and invoke years of experience from the veterans the NATO Officer ordered an attack on the town of Galati. The assault was swift and crushing, with the AAF garrison routing from the town to the Altis Airport, leaving behind numerous weapons and ammunition to help equip newcomers. Seeing the efficiency of the new fighting force, NATO immediately ordered an another daring attack on an AAF Military Base to help establishing a more practical presence of NATO forces countering the looming CSAT threat. Here a number of new recruits can be seen assembling with the returning of Sgt. Nelson due to a lack of leadership. PFC Renaud, The Manticore of Pyrgos, can be seen. Renaud is nicknamed so because of the ridiculous amount of kills he racked up with his marksman rifle during the 2nd Revolution, an astonishing 269 confirmed kills.<br />
<img src="http://i1202.photobucket.com/albums/bb366/thomashung1/107410_20160620033902_1.png" alt="enter image description here" title="enter image title here" /><br />
<img src="http://i1202.photobucket.com/albums/bb366/thomashung1/107410_20160620033914_1.png" alt="enter image description here" title="enter image title here" /><br />
<img src="http://i1202.photobucket.com/albums/bb366/thomashung1/107410_20160620034007_1.png" alt="enter image description here" title="enter image title here" /></p>

<p>While the rebel force was deploying to strike the new AAF Base, the AAF cowardly ordered a sneak attack upon the FIA HQ. Little did they know that NATO had dropped in an MBT the night before. Here's the resulting carnage<br />
<img src="http://i1202.photobucket.com/albums/bb366/thomashung1/107410_20160620041645_1.png" alt="enter image description here" title="enter image title here" /></p>

<p>In their desperation, the AAF keep committing war crimes. They can be seen using workers from a quarry as hostage to deter the freedom fighters from overrunning a resource base just in the outskirts on Kavala. The rebels are preparing to take Kavala, which will provide a huge logistic advantage upon their still weak fighting force<br />
<img src="http://i1202.photobucket.com/albums/bb366/thomashung1/107410_20160620044159_1.png" alt="enter image description here" title="enter image title here" /></p>

<p>Meanwhile, the AAF High Command has brushed away any "threats from rebel scums" and has announced a campaign to "Make Altis Great Again". When questioned how to do that, they didn't answer.<br />
<img src="http://www.armaholic.com/datas/users/serbian_armed_forces_wip08122013_3_4.jpg" alt="enter image description here" title="enter image title here" /></p>

<hr />

<p>The battle for freedom rages on<br />
Ever Forward! (And never trust Greenbacks)</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="Reactions"></div>                    </div>
